<Definitions>
  <Def>
    <Name>Lombardy Poplar</Name>
    <OtherName>Black Poplar</OtherName>
    <ScientificName>Populus nigra 'Italica'</ScientificName>
    <Description>Medium/large narrow, columnar tree with upright branches.  Grows to 60' tall.</Description>
    <Leaves>Green, fine toothed margins.  2" - 4" long/wide.</Leaves>
    <Twigs>Yellow/brown slender, with 1/2" long, glossy buds.</Twigs>
    <SeedConeOrFruit>Fruit:  Fruitless</SeedConeOrFruit>
    <Bark>Gray/green in color becoming furrowed.</Bark>
    <Range>Hardy to zone 4.</Range>
    <Remarks>Short lived.  Often seen along farm drives, although many other columnar poplars exist.</Remarks>
